│ Here are some thoughts about why you want to perform the action.                                                                                                                         │
│ The miscompile comes from initializing NW to GEPNoWrapFlags::all() and then intersecting only with the flags of non-first incoming GEPs. This can add inbounds/nuw to the new GEP even   │
│ if the first incoming GEP lacked them. We should instead initialize NW from the first incoming GEP (FirstInst->getNoWrapFlags()) so that the final flags are the intersection across all │
│ inputs. I will patch InstCombinePHI.cpp accordingly and submit the patch.                                                                                                                │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ sed -i 's/GEPNoWrapFlags NW = GEPNoWrapFlags::all();/GEPNoWrapFlags NW = FirstInst->getNoWrapFlags();/' llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombinePHI.cpp && submit-patch               │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
